FIG. 1 is a side elevation partially see through illustration showing the ball carrier of this invention and the interior mechanism for holding the balls in stacked relation;


FIG. 2 is a front elevation view of the ball carrier of FIG. 1 partially in cross section illustrating the compression mechanism for holding the balls in stacked relation;


FIG. 3 is an enlarged illustration of the top of the carrier of FIGS. 1 and 2 illustrating how a ball is ejected from the carrier by application of downward lateral finger pressure to the top ball of the stack.
